
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Provider {
  - name: String
  - location: String
}

class Cruise {
  - cruiseNumber: String
  - cruiseName: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
}

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class Guest {
  - name: String
  - isVIP: Boolean
}

class Ship {
  - shipName: String
  - numberOfDecks: Integer
  - length: Double
  - passengerCapacity: Integer
}

class TravelAgency {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class Booking {
  - bookingNumber: String
  - bookingDate: Date
}

class DestinationArea {
  - name: String
  - seaName: String
}

class Show {
  - title: String
  - duration: Integer
}

class Ticket {
  - ticketId: String
  - cruise: Cruise "1"
  - guest: Guest "1"
}

Provider "1" -- "0..*" Cruise : organizes
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Employee : requires
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Guest : has
Cruise "1" -- "1" Ship : uses
Cruise "1" -- "1" DestinationArea : heads to
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Show : offers
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Booking : booked via
Booking "1" -- "1" TravelAgency : made by
Guest "0..*" -- "0..*" Ticket : has
Ticket "1" -- "1" Cruise : belongs to
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **Provider** organizes **Cruise**
- **Cruise** requires many **Employees**
- **Cruise** has many **Guests**, and a **Guest** can be in multiple **Cruises**
- **Cruise** uses one **Ship**
- **Cruise** heads to one **DestinationArea**
- **Cruise** offers many **Shows**
- **Cruise** is booked through **Booking**, which is made by a **TravelAgency**
- A **Guest** has many **Tickets**, but only one per **Cruise**
- Each **Ticket** belongs to exactly one **Cruise**

